  * [ Faculty of Science ](https://science.uq.edu.au/home)
  * Be a key member of the Research Management team 
  * Facilitate the dissemination of information and provide advice to researchers 
  * Full-time continuing position 
  * Based at [ St Lucia Campus ](https://campuses.uq.edu.au/)

##  ** About UQ **

As part of the UQ community, you'll have the opportunity to work alongside the
brightest minds, who have joined us from all over the world.  
  
Everyone here has a role to play. As a member of our professional staff
cohort, you will be actively involved in working towards our vision of a
better world. By supporting the academic endeavour across teaching, research,
and the student life, you'll have the opportunity to contribute to activities
that have a lasting impact on our community.  
  
Join a community where excellence is at the core of our culture, contributions
are valued and a range of [ benefits and rewards
](https://careers.uq.edu.au/why-work-at-uq) are available, such as:

  * 26 weeks paid parental leave or 14 weeks paid primary caregiver leave 
  * 17% superannuation contributions 
  * 17.5% annual leave loading 
  * Access to flexible working arrangements including hybrid working options, flexible start/finish times, purchased leave, and a condensed fortnight 
  * Health and wellness discounts - fitness passport access, free yearly flu vaccinations, discounted health insurance, and access to our Employee Assistance Program for staff and their immediate family 
  * On campus childcare options 
  * Cheap parking (from just $5.75 a day) 
  * Salary packaging options 

##  ** About This Opportunity **

The Principal Research Administration Officer facilitates the dissemination of
information and provides advice to researchers on sources of research support,
both external and internal. They also provide high-level assistance to
researchers throughout all stages of the grants and supports the Associate
Dean Research and two Deputy ADRs as appropriate.  
  
Key responsibilities will include:  
  
Research Advisory

  * Act as a senior subject matter expert and source of high-level advice on all aspects of research administration and governance, including: 
    * The research performance and grants profile of the Faculty/Schools/Centres 
    * UQ research-related governance, policies and procedures and any changes or updates 
    * Contribute to briefings, statistics, discussion papers, and/or policy-related documentation arising from the administration of research grants, either in conjunction with other senior staff members or independently 
    * The administration of relevant Faculty Research Committees including bookings, preparation of agenda and minutes and support of implementation of committees' strategies and action plans 
    * Coordination of intermediate and high-complexity internal funding schemes as required, including preparation of guidelines, advertisements, and administration of review and award processes 
    * Providing advice regarding key points of contact within the Faculty/Schools/Centres, the Research Office and other areas of UQ and external to UQ 

Funding and Grant Administration

  * Identify and distribute information regarding research income opportunities as relevant to the specific discipline/context 
  * Plan, organise and participate in research funding seminars/workshops, including as lead/co-lead 
  * Ensure applications are submitted by required deadlines, both internally and externally 
  * Coordinate review of research grant applications through the Faculty Readership scheme including the appointment and management of readers and scheme finances 
  * Assist with Faculty consideration of requests for research co-investment 

Communication and engagement

  * Design and maintain research webpages and intranet sites to ensure that academic staff have access to relevant information on grants, events, seminars and workshops 
  * Assist in the promotion of Faculty/Schools/Centres research activity on websites 
  * Support communication of research-related information through preparation of a fortnightly Faculty Research e-newsletter 
  * Oversee delivery of researcher development events such as seminars, workshops and research days including arranging bookings, promotion, approvals and payments 
  * Administer the Faculty Researcher Mentoring Scheme 
  * Establish strong and effective networks across UQ to develop consistent approaches to research administration 

This is a full-time (100%), continuing position.  
  
At HEW level 7, the full-time equivalent base salary will be in the range
$96,649.64 - $105,244.58, plus a generous super allowance of up to 17%. The
total FTE package will be up to $113,080.08 - $123,136.15 annually. As this
role is covered by an Enterprise Agreement, you will also receive regular
remuneration increases - at least once a year.

##  ** About You **

  * Completion of a degree with at least four years subsequent relevant experience; OR Extensive experience and management expertise; OR 
  * An equivalent combination of relevant experience and/or education/training. 
  * Demonstrated and well-advanced experience of research administration or research management 
  * Proficiency at an advanced level using computer software packages for word-processing, data storage and retrieval, and spreadsheets as well as a high level of proficiency and practical understanding of administrative computer applications, especially with data on mainframe corporate systems 
  * Excellent written and interpersonal communication skills 
  * Detailed knowledge of higher education policies and procedures in relation to research administration, or demonstrated capacity to gain this knowledge 
  * Demonstrated experience in the development of strong external and internal relationships 
  * Demonstrated ability to generate and write briefings, strategic reports, and/or policy papers with a high attention to detail, either in conjunction with other senior staff members or independently 
  * Integrity, diplomacy and sensitivity in communicating with a range of client groups 
  * Ability to work cooperatively and constructively with staff from within a variety of settings from within the University and external to the University 
  * Excellent abilities as a team player 

In addition, the following mandatory requirements apply:

  * ** Work Rights: ** You must have unrestricted work rights in Australia for the duration of this appointment to apply. Visa sponsorship is not available for this appointment. 
  * ** Background Checks: ** All final applicants for this position may be asked to consent to a criminal record check. Please note that people with criminal records are not automatically barred from applying for this position. Each application will be considered on its merits. 

